    541 EST Element Summary Table Main Index Notes 1.This record is actually not describable, since the element is not repeated with each occurrence. A compiler change is the entry repeats until eor without rechecking the ‘OR’ sequences. The mop at the end will at least allow the first occurrence on each record to be printed correctly and no error messages will be triggered . 2.There are conflicts among document versions that require straightening out by ‘masters’ of the applications. 3.Words 4, 5 and 6 are defined as follows: Open core names for elements in EMG are defined as /EMGXII/ where II is an integer from 1 to 48 associated with a particular element type. The current numbers by element are as follows: Element II Element II Element II Element II ROD 01 MASS2 02 ELAS2 02 DUM5 27 DAMP2 02 FLMASS 04 unused 05 unused 14 unused 17 HEX20 22 AERO 00 GAP 20 DUM9 27 MASS3 02 ELAS3 02 DUM6 27 BEAM 06 AXIF2 04 QUAD4 10 unused 14 DAMP3 02 HEXA 24 TRIAX6 21 TETRA 30 unused 17 unused 14 unused 03 DUM7 27 unused 15 MASS4 02 ELAS4 02 DAMP1 02 TUBE 01 AXIF3 04 BAR 12 unused 17 DAMP4 02 PENTA 24 unused 21 DUM8 27 FLUID2 04 unused 14 TRIA3 08 unused 16 CONM1 11 unused 14 SHEAR 13 AXIF4 04 CONEAX 28 VISC 11 BEND 29 DUM3 27 FLUID3 04 CONROD 01 TRIA6 09 QUAD8 23 CONM2 11 unused 14 MASS1 02 SLOT3 04 unused 18 FLUID4 04 ELAS1 02 DUM4 27 unused 22 PLOTEL 00 unused 14 unused 14 SLOT4 unused 19 4.Each value defines a bit number.
